sentences: Kim Hyo-yeon (born September 22, 1989), referred to as Hyoyeon or DJ Hyo, is a South Korean singer, dancer, DJ, and television personality.
She debuted as a member of the girl group Girls' Generation in August 2007, which went on to become one of the best-selling artists in South Korea and one of the most popular K-pop groups worldwide.
Since 2016, she has also released singles as a solo artist.
Hyoyeon was born in Incheon, South Korea on September 22, 1989.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: In 1999, she enrolled in Winners Dance School, a famous dance school in South Korea specializing in popping, locking, animation and various other hip-hop styles.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: At the school she met Miss A's Min, with whom she formed the dance team Little Winners (리틀위너스).
section: == Early life ==

sentences: The duo performed at various showcases and was spotlighted by HipHoper.com in 2004.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: Hyoyeon auditioned for SM Entertainment at the age of 11 through the SM 2000 Casting System.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: In 2004, along with Super Junior's Siwon, she was sent to study Chinese in Beijing.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: Before debuting with Girls' Generation, she worked with a choreographer for Janet Jackson and was BoA's silhouette dancer during a performance at M.net KM Music Festival 2005.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: In 2007, she teamed up with Jae Won for a dance collaboration to "Anonymous".

sentences: In April 2012, Hyoyeon became a contestant in the second season of Dancing with the Stars, a competitive ballroom dancing television show.
